Another most repeatededly question in Interview
===================================================

Q. For suppose i  have 10 tasks now i wnat to execute all these 10 tasks means i will give command as ansible-playbook filename
But in these 10 tasks need to be execute only 9 tasks and 1 task should not be execute how can you do that

for this situation we will use TAGS
=======================================

vim babu.yml

----
- hosts: dev
  connection: ssh

  tasks:
     - name: install scm tool
       yum: name=git state=present

     - name: install java17
       yum: name=java-17-amazon-corretto state=present

     - name: install maven
       yum: name=maven state=present

     - name: install httpd
       yum: name=httpd state=present

:wq

Now for the above playbook i need to be skip maven installation for that we will use tags like below
                                                                                    ============

vim babu.yml

----
- hosts: dev
  connection: ssh

  tasks:
     - name: install scm tool
       yum: name=git state=present

     - name: install java17
       yum: name=java-17-amazon-corretto state=present

     - name: install maven
       yum: name=maven state=present
       tags: buildtool(give tagname here)

     - name: install httpd
       yum: name=httpd state=present

:wq

ansible-playbook babu.yml --skip-tags=buildtool--------------> command to execute playbook and using tags to skip a particular task in yaml playbook file


For suppose if we want to skip multiple tasks means 
=======================================================

vim bbau.yml

---
- hosts: dev
  connection: ssh
  
  tasks:
    - name: install scm tool
      yum: name=git state=present
      
    - name: install jav17
      yum: name=java-17-amazon-corretto state=present
      tags: java
      
    - name: install maven
      yum: name=maven state=present
      
    - name: install httpd
      yum: name=httpd state=present

:wq

ansible-playbook babu.yml --skip-tags="buildtool, java"------------> command to execute playbook and using tags to skip a particular task in yaml playbook file

For suppose scenario vice-versa case

ex: if i have 10 tasks i want to execute 9 tasks as remaining 1 task should need to be skip

